    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-09-05T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-09-05T12:00:00-05:00" n="763"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d763">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">119.2/3005a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Atherton</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-09-05T13:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 5, 1935—1 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>242. In order to assure the continuance of telegraphic communications with
                    Ethiopia this Government contemplates installing a radio sending and receiving
                    set at the Legation at Addis Ababa. In order to relay messages to Washington it
                    would be necessary to station an American war vessel in nearby waters. Please
                    ascertain whether the British authorities would have any objection to the
                    presence at Aden of an American cruiser which is the smallest vessel having
                    radio equipment capable of communication with Washington. If you consider it
                    desirable you may add that this vessel might also be used in case of emergency
                    to assist in the evacuation of American nationals from Ethiopia.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
